            "content_html": "\n<p>The Indian film industry is an entirely different pinnacle of opulence. Every celebrity goes out of their way to look presentable. Their appearance is always a delight for our eyes, whether it is an airport look or a dinner scene at their favourite restaurant. Picture what these celebrities\u2019 abodes would look like with such splendor, right? Each celebrity has a lavish lifestyle, which we are aware of. They take the opportunity to splurge&nbsp;an exorbitant amount of money in order to live a life of luxury and glamour. We have all heard of Shah Rukh Khan&#8217;s &#8220;Mannat,&#8221; Amitabh Bachchan&#8217;s &#8220;Jalsa,&#8221; and John Abraham&#8217;s &#8220;Villa In The Sky.&#8221; Rohit Shetty is the most recent celebrity to join the premium house party in Mumbai.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While most celebrities buy magnificent homes or villas after becoming wealthy, famous Bollywood director-producer Rohit Shetty has gone a notch up and purchased a whole building. The director has acquired a 10-story property in Juhu, one of Mumbai&#8217;s most affluent neighborhoods. Juhu is a renowned neighborhood where several well-known celebrities have luxury houses. You may easily come across spectacular bungalows and extravagant flats with beautiful gardens and luxurious facilities that will astound anybody who passes by. Renowned Bollywood filmmaker, Rohit Shetty\u2019s house is one such luxurious example. Shetty\u2019s skyscraper was originally called Ishaan after his son, but now has a \u201cShetty Tower\u201d sign on the entrance.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-rohit-shetty-home-what-s-inside-this-luxurious-tower\"><strong>Rohit Shetty Home: What\u2019s Inside This Luxurious Tower?</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image-1-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-30889\" srcset=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image-1-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.squareyards.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.squareyards.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.squareyards.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://www.squareyards.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image-1-2048x1365.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>According to sources, Rohit Shetty and his family have moved into the 10-story tower&#8217;s top two levels. Rohit Shetty&#8217;s Mumbai house, named &#8220;Shetty Tower,&#8221; is reported to be Rohit Shetty&#8217;s dream house. The filmmaker of &#8220;Golmaal&#8221; had planned to develop a home in one of Mumbai&#8217;s finest areas for eleven years, and his hard work and commitment had finally paid off.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every Bollywood fan knows Rohit Shetty&#8217;s passion for automobiles, and we have seen his blockbuster films feature a diverse range of vehicles. As a result, the filmmaker has decided to devote the first four levels of his 10-story celebrity mansion to his high-end vehicle collection. Lamborghini Urus, Maserati GT Sport, Ford Mustang GT (2016), Range Rover, and BMW 7-Series (earlier version) are among his premium vehicles. You should also be aware that Rohit Shetty enjoys customizing his automobiles. This is why most vehicles, like the Ford Mustang GT and Range Rover, have extra features and distinctive colours. Each of these vehicles would cost between 1.2 and 2 crores.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first four and top two levels of Rohit Shetty&#8217;s house are allocated to his family and vehicles, while the other levels will be rented, according to people close to the filmmaker.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another source close to Rohit Shetty told a leading weekly newspaper, &#8220;Rohit has a completely operational workplace with terrace-seating and a production house in Andheri and would not be relocating his workstation into the new tower.\u201d This is his new residence, where he lives with his mother, Ratna, his wife, Maya, and their son, Ishaan.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rohit Shetty&#8217;s Mumbai residence was completed last year, and it has a large lawn as well as a high-end security cabin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-a-brief-overview-of-shetty-tower-s-architecture\"><strong>A Brief Overview of Shetty Tower\u2019s Architecture</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Located on Hasya Kalakar Mehmood Chowk in Juhu, Shetty Tower stands tall over other structures and can easily be distinguished. The residence of Rohit Shetty is a wonderful example of contemporary architecture. He has designed his house in a simple yet appealing manner. The Shetty Tower is a structure that prioritizes utility and a clean aesthetic over ornamentation. The design style differs from that of more ornately adorned residences. The tower is strewn with sprawling verandahs on each floor and the same are embellished with plants. In a hectic metropolis like Mumbai, it is important that one&#8217;s house feels like a getaway, with adequate natural light and fresh air to breathe. Rohit Shetty&#8217;s abode meets all of these requirements. Owing to the multiple floor-to-ceiling glass doors installed on the verandahs, the filmmaker&#8217;s residence transforms into a sun-drenched bliss throughout the day. The house&#8217;s elegant appearance is enhanced by the sunshine pouring on it during the daytime.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Shetty Tower also has a sprawling home garden inside, which contains diverse families of plants adding to the house&#8217;s appeal. Plants are also known to help with stress reduction, which might explain the reason for the ever so joyous look on Shetty&#8217;s face. Apart from the interiors, the exteriors are equally adorned with lush greenery, making the top half of the structure peep over the various trees. The house&#8217;s visually pleasing appearance is always enhanced by the modern architectural aspect combined with the natural surroundings. The general tone of the house is very well-coordinated, and all of the building&#8217;s components are interconnected in a way that adds to its charm.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Aside from the aforementioned amenities, the Shetty Tower also possesses the highest level of security. Emergency buzzers, intercoms, escape chute and top-of-the-line security installations guarantee the Shetty family a hassle-free life.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-celebrity-neighbors-of-rohit-shetty-celeb-homes-in-juhu\"><strong>Celebrity Neighbors of Rohit Shetty | Celeb Homes in Juhu</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Juhu has long been one of Mumbai&#8217;s affluent suburbs, and it is home to some of the city&#8217;s greatest superstars. Among those with whom Rohit Shetty shares the same street are:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Shatrughan Sinha:</strong> This nine-story celebrity home, named &#8220;Ramayan,&#8221; is just next door to Rohit Shetty&#8217;s building. \u201cRamayan\u201d is a fitting name for Sinha\u2019s residence since Shatrugan Sinha&#8217;s brothers are Ram, Bharat, and Laxman, and Sonakshi Sinha&#8217;s brothers are Luv and Kush.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Amitabh Bachchan:</strong> Amitabh Bachchan, often known as &#8220;Bollywood&#8217;s Shehenshah,&#8221; is a resident of this plush neighbourhood, where he owns two homes, &#8220;Prateeksha&#8221; and &#8220;Jalsa.&#8221; Not only do Amitabh and his family have several palatial properties in Mumbai, but they also own a couple of lavish properties in other places across the world. Amitabh Bachchan, Jaya Bachchan, Abhishek Bachchan, Aishwarya Rai Bachchan, and Aaradhya Bachchan possess multi-crore residences ranging from five houses in Mumbai to a posh flat in Paris.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Shakti Kapoor:</strong> Shakti Kapoor, one of Bollywood&#8217;s most notorious villains, lives with his family on Gandhigram Road in Juhu. Apart from Juhu, Shakti Kapoor also has properties on Madh Island, Lonavala, and Greater Kailash, Delhi.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Hema Malini:</strong> Bollywood&#8217;s &#8220;Dream Girl&#8221; Hema Malini lives in Juhu&#8217;s Jai Hind society and shares a neighborhood with Rohit Shetty. Surrounded by lush greenery and breathtaking skyline \u2014 her home radiates a peaceful vibe, becoming an escape from the hustle and bustle of Mumbai city.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Ajay Devgn:</strong> Actor-producer Ajay Devgn lives at Sheetal Apartments in Juhu with his actress wife Kajol and two kids. The couple has named their residence Shivshakti and in comparison to other famous mansions in Juhu, the property has a highly ornate facade. The mansion is decorated in neutral tones, with grand staircases and ornate light fixtures.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Hrithik Roshan:</strong> The Mumbai house of the &#8220;Dhoom&#8221; star, named &#8220;Paras,&#8221; is located on Juhu Road. The luxurious mansion, valued at 500 million rupees, is a famous celebrity home in the neighbourhood. The actor&#8217;s life and taste are reflected in the 3000 Sq. Ft home, which has a den and two bedrooms.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Interesting Facts About Him: Rohit Shetty\u2019s Many Achievements</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rohit Shetty was born in Mumbai, India, on March 14, 1973. He is presently one of India&#8217;s highest-paid directors and a permanent member of the highest-grossing films club. Shetty began his career as an assistant director to Kuku Kohli on Ajay Devgn&#8217;s debut film, Phool Aur Kaante, when he was 17 years old. He had some prior knowledge about the Hindi film industry, thanks to his parents, Ratna Shetty and M.B Shetty, who both were actors and have worked in Bollywood. Across many media appearances, the director has recounted living in an apartment in Dahisar, earning \u20b935 per day, going through an economic meltdown, and taking the Mumbai local to get to work on time. Since then, he has directed blockbusters like Golmaal and Singham, as well as commercial hits like Chennai Express and Bol Bachchan.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is difficult to say how much Shetty&#8217;s property is worth, but it will almost certainly be a lot of money, given that property prices in this area range from Rs 50,000 to Rs 80,000 per Sq. Ft. According to sources, his house is believed to be worth approximately \u20b96 crores. Shetty also has a number of real-estate holdings around the country.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rohit Shetty&#8217;s overall net worth is believed to be $ 38 million, which is about \u20b9280 crore in Indian currency (that is- INR 280 crore). In the last several years, Rohit Shetty&#8217;s net worth has increased by 58%. Mr Shetty&#8217;s net worth is made up of movie earnings, personal investments, and his production company, \u201cRohit Shetty Production House Pvt. Ltd.\u201d one of the biggest production companies in Bollywood. Apart from films, television has also contributed significantly to Rohit Shetty&#8217;s net worth. On television, the filmmaker has appeared as a judge/host on series such as Comedy Circus and Khatron Ke Khiladi. According to rumours, Shetty was paid 30 lakhs to host Khatron Ke Khiladi in 2019 and would be paid 1 crore to feature in the show this year.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a philanthropist, he is one of the most prominent figures when it comes to giving to a good cause and charity. He is also one of the country&#8217;s significant taxpayers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-ending-remarks\"><strong>Ending Remarks</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Without a producer, Bollywood cinema would be incomplete. \u201cIf there is no producer, there are no movies,\u201d said one well-known figure. Bollywood films rely heavily on film production to succeed, and Rohit Shetty is one such producer and director who has propelled Hindi cinema to new heights.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rohit Shetty has had numerous ups and downs in his career, including a period when he was in the midst of a financial crisis. He, on the other hand, bounced back with renewed vigour and demonstrated his value to the world in the most effective manner imaginable. He currently owns a beautiful property in a Mumbai suburb neighborhood and lives there with his family.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rohit Shetty bought this property in 2013 and has steadily transformed it into the grandeur it is now. Shetty has tried to keep its design relative to modern trends. His residence is one of the most sought-after celebrity residences in Mumbai, with admirers flocking to see it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to sources, the filmmaker had originally intended to settle down in Goa and only step out of his sweet paradise for work purposes, which includes making trips to Mumbai and other cities. The Shetty Tower was supposed to be just another investment venture. Thankfully, that hasn&#8217;t happened, and the tower has added to Juhu&#8217;s already lavish landscape.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-faqs\"><strong>FAQs</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>1.<strong>What is the address of Rohit Shetty&#8217;s home?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rohit Shetty&#8217;s home is in Mumbai&#8217;s affluent Juhu neighborhood.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2.<strong>What is the number of storeys in Rohit Shetty&#8217;s home?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The residence of Rohit Shetty has a total of ten storeys.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3.<strong>In Mumbai, who is Rohit Shetty&#8217;s next-door neighbour?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Mumbai, Shatrughan Sinha is Rohit Shetty&#8217;s next-door neighbour.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4.<strong>What is Rohit Shetty\u2019s Net worth?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rohit Shetty&#8217;s net worth is 250 crores rupees.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>5.<strong>What is Rohit Shetty\u2019s Mumbai residence called?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rohit Shetty\u2019s Mumbai residence was initially named after his son Ishaan but has now been renamed into the \u201cShetty Tower.\u201d</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/all-about-shetty-tower-rohit-shettys-luxurious-residence-at-juhu\">All About Shetty Tower: Rohit Shetty\u2019s Luxurious Residence at Juhu</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog\">Real Estate News</a>.</p>\n",
