            "content_html": "<p>The <em>God of Cricket</em>, Sachin Tendulkar, needs no introduction. There has been immense interest in knowing about <strong>Sachin Tendulkar house</strong>s in Mumbai and overall <strong>Sachin Tendulkar property</strong> in India. <strong>Sachin\u2019s house </strong>was earlier in a plush apartment complex. However, the new <strong>Sachin Tendulkar home</strong>s in Mumbai are a bungalow and luxurious apartment respectively. One <strong>Sachin house </strong>is at Perry Cross Road at Bandra West. This <strong>Sachin Tendulkar house in Mumbai </strong>and the family\u2019s primary residence, covers a massive 6,000 square feet. The <strong>Sachin Tendulkar house price </strong>was reportedly around Rs. 39 crore which the superstar paid for buying the plot in the year 2007. He has spent another 40-45 crores on renovations and transforming the dilapidated villa that once sat on this plot, into the imposing 5-storied villa that we see today.</p>\n<p>Another <strong>Sachin house in Mumbai </strong>is the lavish property that he purchased for Anjali Tendulkar, his wife, in Mumbai. This <strong>Sachin Tendulkar house address</strong> is at Rustomjee Seasons in the BKC (Bandra-Kurla Complex) and the <strong>Tendulkar house</strong> reportedly cost around Rs. 7.5 crore. This is a spacious 1600 square feet apartment with luxurious amenities and facilities. Interestingly, sometime earlier, an Anjali <strong>Tendulkar house</strong> in the ultra-prime Malabar Hill, Mumbai, was sold to a businessman for a whopping sum of Rs. 145 crore. <em>Mehta House</em>, this property, belonged to her parents.</p>\n<h3><strong>Sachin Tendulkar house facts </strong></h3>\n<p>The current <strong>Sachin Tendulkar home in Mumbai </strong>was reconstructed after he purchased the plot in the year 2007 at Perry Cross Road. He shifted into this property with his family in the year 2011. The overall <strong>Sachin home </strong>cost thus stands at upwards of Rs. 80 crore. The pre-independence property housed a classic Paris villa and it is now a sprawling villa with five floors and 1 \u00bd floors remain underground as per BMC guidelines pertaining to the heights of buildings. The bungalow lies along one of Mumbai\u2019s most prime locations with a view of the Arabian Sea as well.</p>\n<p>The area is home to numerous celebrities and movie stars alike. Sachin Tendulkar has reportedly taken out an insurance policy of Rs. 100 crore for this property, inclusive of Rs. 75 crore in fire insurance and added coverage of Rs. 25 crore for its interiors. This policy also offers coverage for damages owing to acts of God like earthquakes, terrorism and other activities like bomb blasts, burglaries and so on. Items like the compound walls, cost of the land of the bungalow, security installations, water reservoir and electrical equipment are also covered under this insurance plan. The 3-storied mansion comes with two basements and they can readily house 40-50 cars together. There is a secondary kitchen on the upper basement along with the servant quarters and a master surveillance zone for security requirements.</p>\n<p>There is a high-walled fence for this property which restricts outside views and the ground floor has a temple where the star cricketer\u2019s mother spends a lot of her time. The kitchen is sleek with a contemporary cook-top and granite countertop while the cricketer has his favorite corner in the bungalow where he records a majority of his videos on Instagram. He relaxes in the garden area as well which has a small sitting area or cabana where he records messages. Numerous lovely paintings adorn the home and the huge living room comes with brown and white hues. The living room has premium couches with vibrant cushions and the ceiling is close to 20 feet! The bungalow also comes with a glass bridge linking the lobby of two separate structures in reality. One side has the master bedroom and the other side has the rooms of the children. The bungalow has a big garden with rows and rows of shrubs, palm trees, tropical plants, a small pond and succulents.</p>\n<h3><strong>Sachin Tendulkar\u2019s Mumbai apartment- Key Facts</strong></h3>\n<p>Sachin Tendulkar purchased a lavish apartment in Rustomjee Seasons, BKC, for his wife Anjali Tendulkar sometime earlier. This home has been designed by the Singapore-based interior design firm, Etho Space. The apartment has been designed painstakingly with environment-friendly features as well and the best construction technologies. The interiors sport an earthy look and feel which is stylish while the kitchen flaunts a minimalistic design theme with modern amenities.</p>\n<p>The living room is cozy and aesthetically appealing, particularly for its artistically designed and contemporary interiors. There are plush furnishings adorning the living room which lend a whole new elegance to the look. The study is themed in black with a classy touch to it and a world map positioned upon a wall in tandem with accompanying glass doors all around. This is a great meeting space for the couple. The apartment also comes with its own terrace that may be viewed from all the study and living room alike.</p>\n<h3><strong>FAQs</strong></h3>\n\n        <section class=\"sc_fs_faq sc_card\">\n            <div>\n\t\t\t\t<h2>Where does Sachin Tendulkar live?</h2>                <div>\n\t\t\t\t\t                    <p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tSachin Tendulkar lives in Bandra West and also owns another apartment at the Bandra-Kurla Complex (BKC).                    </p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </section>\n\t        <section class=\"sc_fs_faq sc_card\">\n            <div>\n\t\t\t\t<h2>What is Sachin Tendulkar\u2019s home address?</h2>                <div>\n\t\t\t\t\t                    <p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tThe address is 19-A, Perry Cross Road, Bandra West.                    </p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </section>\n\t\n<script type=\"app