            "title": "Nana Patekar\u2019s simple and unconventional house reflects his personality",
            "content_html": "<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><em><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Among many renowned&nbsp;celebs,&nbsp;Nana Patekar&nbsp;is one of the most genuine and unpretentious celebrities in Bollywood. He is well regarded by celebs owing to his excellent craft and simplistic personality. And, among a few&nbsp;celebrity homes,&nbsp;Nana Patekar\u2019s house&nbsp;also speaks of simplicity.&nbsp;</span></em><em><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></em></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Nana Patekar</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;owns many properties across the country including a&nbsp;<strong>farmhouse</strong>&nbsp;in Khadakwasla near&nbsp;<strong>Pune</strong>, and he lives in a 1BHK apartment in&nbsp;<strong>Andheri</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Mumbai</strong>. He also owns a bungalow in&nbsp;<strong>Murud&nbsp;</strong>as well as a stylish home in&nbsp;<strong>Goa</strong>&nbsp;because he keeps on travelling there from time to time. Though the&nbsp;<strong>celebrity homes&nbsp;</strong>are usually<strong>&nbsp;</strong>luxurious and always up to the mark,&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar\u2019s house</strong>&nbsp;is simple and unconventional.&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Having debuted in 1979,&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;has given four decades to the Indian Film Industry and has worked in numerous films. He has always been a versatile actor and also a successful one. Leading an effortless and unpretentious lifestyle, the successful celeb lives in a one-room apartment. This alone signifies the down-to-earth nature of&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>.</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<h2 style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><strong><u><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Nana Patekar, an astounding actor-</span></u></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></h2>\n<p></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Nana Patekar</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;is one of those prized actors of our country who got India\u2019s fourth-highest civilian award, the Padma Shri. Being a method actor<strong>, Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;is versatile and can nail every role to perfection. Patekar is known to be one of the few celebrities who got the Filmfare award for the Best Actor, Best Actor in Supporting Role, and the Best Villain. It was never a doubt to anyone if&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;can play a role or not in a particular film. Since then, having debuted in the movie &#8220;Gaman &#8221; in 1979,&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;has played several characters in the Indian Film Industry<strong>.&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Nana Patekar</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;has been highly praised for his role in the film &#8220;Salaam Bombay&#8221; in 1988, and he won a National award for the best supporting role in the movie &#8220;Parinda&#8221; in 1989. N<strong>ana Patekar&nbsp;</strong>is not only an actor, but he is also a writer, a screenwriter, a filmmaker, and a philanthropist. While perfecting his role in Prahaar,&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;had gone through rigorous army training for three years, for which he was given the honorary title of &#8220;Captain&#8221; in the 1990s. He has worked in many great films such as Krantiveer, Ab Tak Chhapan, Taxi No 9 2 11, Yeshwant, etc., and has successfully entranced the audience in every walk of his career. The actor mainly worked in Hindi and Marathi films.&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<h2 style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\">Nana Patekar,a true philanthropist-&nbsp;</h2>\n<p></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Even though&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;is an amazing actor and a great filmmaker, he never made a show of his generosity and philanthropy, keeping his personal life and kind deeds to himself.&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;had stepped himself up for the farmers of Maharashtra when they were suffering in unimaginable ways. During the Vidharba drought in 2015<strong>, Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;had hugely supported the farmers in Maharashtra. He has generously donated to the families of farmers who had committed suicide and gave a cheque of INR 15,000 to almost 62 families in Maharashtra<strong>. Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;has personally visited 112 families in Latur during the period of drought to inspect their conditions and extended a helping hand to them.&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<h2 style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">The Naam Foundation-</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></h2>\n<p></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Nana Patekar</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">, along with Makarand Anaspune, created the Naam Foundation in September 2015. It was founded considering the negligence towards the devastating drought situations in Maharashtra and the increase in the number of farmer suicides due to the drought. The constant water crisis in those areas led to the rapid degeneration of the villages in Maharashtra. The villagers and the farmers were not getting safe drinking water, let alone the water to cultivate.</span><span style=\"color: #0e101a; font-size: inherit;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">And, the climatic conditions of those regions were also not in favour of the farmers. Being a true philanthropist and humanitarian,&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;founded the Naam Foundation as a response to the problems of the farmers. The Naam Foundation seeks to educate the farmers, reviving the canals and abandoned water projects in that area, and restoring the groundwater. The major aim of the Naam Foundation is to fill up the dried lakes and rivers and provide safe and clean drinking water to the people of Maharashtra. As per his efforts, many of the above prospects have successfully been completed.</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">The Naam Foundation has already managed to collect INR 22 lakhs for the farmers\u2019 welfare from many people<strong>. Nana Patekar</strong> himself has donated almost 90% of his earnings to charity till now. The Naam Foundation can connect the people to the areas as far as Nagpur, Latur, Hingoli, Parbhani, Nanded, Aurangabad, etc. And has evolved from a movement to an organization facilitating developments in the villages of Maharashtra.</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<h2 style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">The houses in which Nana Patekar lives and the lifestyle he leads-</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></h2>\n<p></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Nana Patekar&nbsp;</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">was born and brought up in&nbsp;<strong>Murud,</strong>&nbsp;Maharashtra and his father passed away at the age of 28 years. Even though he reportedly has assets of INR 40 crores, he lives a very simple life. The lifestyle he leads is a reflection of his way of living. Currently,&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar\u2019s house</strong>&nbsp;is a 1BHK apartment in&nbsp;<strong>Andheri, Mumbai&nbsp;</strong>which he formerly used to share with his mother. Most&nbsp;<strong>celebs</strong>&nbsp;prefer to have costly and comfortable houses so they can flex about it. This contradicts the way Nana<strong>&nbsp;Patekar</strong>&nbsp;leads his lifestyle in his 1BHK apartment in&nbsp;<strong>Andheri, Mumbai</strong>. It explains how he leads his lifestyle because his simple home is surely a down-to-earth attribute.&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&#8216;s achievements in the entirety of his career and still counting are like a golden feather in his cap as he is a great philanthropist and has great empathy towards the people in trouble.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Even if he is a great artist compared to none, he leads a straightforward life and dresses quite plainly.</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">A few years ago, <strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;had purchased a&nbsp;<strong>farmhouse</strong>&nbsp;in Khadakwasla, which is near&nbsp;<strong>Pune.</strong>&nbsp;That place is very peaceful and calm, away from the chaos of the city. One can go there and spend a relaxing vacation in that farmhouse.&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar&nbsp;</strong>spends most of his time in that&nbsp;<strong>farmhouse</strong>&nbsp;in Khadakwasla, as it is situated in a peaceful area. The&nbsp;<strong>farmhouse&nbsp;</strong>has an area of 27 acres and is a beautiful place. Complimenting his simple personality, he also likes to live in a calming and peaceful place. Speaking of&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar\u2019s farmhouse</strong>, it has seven rooms and a large hall. Although it is a large house, the interior of the&nbsp;<strong>farmhouse</strong>&nbsp;is very subtle and nothing fancy&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;has never been materialistic in his whole life and has great concern for the people.&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;is such a man who can claim that he has donated almost 90% of his earnings to the charity.</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Reports claim that&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;cultivates paddy and wheat in his&nbsp;<strong>farmhouse at Pune</strong>&nbsp;and sells the crop collected throughout the state. Afterward, he would distribute all the money among the workers in the fields at the&nbsp;<strong>farmhouse</strong>. This has been an employment source to many people. The generosity he holds is incomparable and cannot be measured through materialistic means.&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Earlier, it was confirmed that&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;had bought a house in&nbsp;<strong>Murud</strong>. The house is a lovely bungalow situated on Law College Road in&nbsp;<strong>Pune.</strong>&nbsp;It was recognized to be the same bungalow where he used to sneak into its backyard and steal Indian plums and white jam in his childhood.&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;seems to commemorate his past and childhood memories through these activities<strong>. Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;was known to have a difficult childhood as his father died at 28 years. His father used to be posted in&nbsp;<strong>Mumbai</strong>, but&nbsp;<strong>Nana Patekar</strong>&nbsp;and his siblings were living in&nbsp;<strong>Murud</strong>&nbsp;along with their mother. But, he has kept his childhood happy moments through these possessions.</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Nana Patekar</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">&nbsp;has become a brand name of simplicity and compassion. Despite being a versatile actor, a great filmmaker, a screenwriter, he has never forgotten his roots and his people. He is a great humanitarian who has never been indulged in any form of social biases. His Naam Foundation has done a great job in facilitating development and welfare in various regions of Maharashtra. And after all that he has done to his country and his people, he still lives in a 1BHK apartment in&nbsp;<strong>Andheri</strong>&nbsp;like a simple man. This is too little of possession for an artist of his caliber, but he seems to be too content in the lifestyle he leads and will continue to work for his people.</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<h2>FAQs</h2>\n<p></p>\n\n        <section class=\"sc_fs_faq sc_card\">\n            <div>\n\t\t\t\t<h2>How many houses does Nana Patekar own? </h2>                <div>\n\t\t\t\t\t                    <p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tNana Patekar owns a bungalow in Pune and one house in Goa. He has bought a farmhouse in Khadakwasla near Pune and lives in a 1BHK apartment in Andheri, Mumbai.                    </p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </section>\n\t        <section class=\"sc_fs_faq sc_card\">\n            <div>\n\t\t\t\t<h2>How many acres is the farmhouse that Nana Patekar owns?</h2>                <div>\n\t\t\t\t\t 