            "content_text": "Celebrity homes are as soothing to the eyes as the sound of the ocean to the ears. Many times we see celebrity homes as goals, but let&#8217;s make one thing clear, that is, no dream home comes to you all of a sudden. Just like every posh homeowner, one has to be working hard enough to make a living so lavish and glamorous. Welcome to Suriya and Jyothika&#8217;s home! Without further ado, let&#8217;s take a tour of their ultra-luxurious abode.\nJyothika and Suriya&#8217;s Family-\nSuriya is a well-known Indian Film Actor and producer, married to Jyothika, who has been announced as Zee Tamil Channel&#8217;s first-ever brand Ambassador. They have children named Dev and Diya. The actor plus producer&#8217;s first film was Nerrukku Ner in 1997 and that&#8217;s not it. Quite a number of films have gotten Suriya and Jyothika&#8217;s family their top-notch, merging style abode. This celebrity home consists of spaces one can surely dream about and work towards. So if you have no idea what your dream home should look like, let us take you through a tour in and around the celebrity home that is situated in Chennai\u2019s poshest locality. The actor, as we know, emerges from a huge acting background with father being an actor, brother, Karthik Sivakumar a successful actor, and sister, Brindha Sivakumar, who is a singer in the Indian film industry. Coming from a background filled with actors and singers, Suriya sure had his way through the industry as we all know that talent and skills never go unnoticed. He has and will always be known for his brilliant acting skills and his nurturing nature towards people.\nAGARAM Foundation- \nSuriya Sivakumar also brings hope to the world by opening a charity organization for the under-privileged providing them quality education. The Foundation is known as Agaram Foundation and is founded by the actor himself where people from all over the world can contribute to help the underprivileged children. Agaram Vidhai is a part of the foundation where the under-privileged are not only given quality education but are also given mentoring, training workshops, employability and placement training to help succeed in life.\nThis foundation also helps people get jobs as they hire candidates or volunteers to help provide services to the underprivileged. The mission of this beautifully created foundation is to build new opportunities for the new generation of responsible youth by providing quality education, values, commitment, and dedication to society.\nInteresting facts about Jyothika and Suriya Shivakumar&#8217;s Abode\nSuriya&#8217;s home is not just massive, but it is lavish, mixing the concept of style and elegance, but there&#8217;s surely more to it than just being lavish, isn&#8217;t there? Suriya and Jyothika Shivakumar&#8217;s family now resides in a bungalow situated in Chennai. The bungalow is located on Vijayalakshmi Street which is known to be one of the poshest areas in Chennai. Suriya and Jyothika\u2019s home is exposed to lush greens and Chennai\u2019s skyline.\nThe garden, perfectly landscaped, is situated right at the entrance which in turn gives Jyothika and Suriya&#8217;s home a welcoming appeal. Jyothika&#8217;s family has set up the garden so beautifully with flowers and plants which seem to also welcome a variety of birds. Imagine waking up to a chirping sound- a pure bliss! The garden in Jyothika and Suriya&#8217;s home is also where Suriya spends most of his time playing with his children.\nAs the house opens up, we get to see their bungalow&#8217;s lavish living room where Suriya is mostly seen spending his free time post his shoots. Suriya and his family spend most of their time bonding in that living area and not just that, Jyothika&#8217;s gatherings are also a part of the living area.\nThe living room is seen to have elegant and various artworks on its walls along with antiques on tabletops, and Divans for relaxing. Divans is a type of bed with only a thick base to lie but has no frame at either end. Jyothika and Suriya&#8217;s home is a home where interiors have out-marked the rest, with well-lit and soothing to the eye home decor.\nLet&#8217;s bring the flooring in the picture now &#8211; The floors are seen to be designed with quality marble that literally shines like glass. Imagine walking on glass, which is what walking around in Jyothika and Suriya&#8217;s home feels like.\nMoving on to the kitchen, the lavish living area now leads you to the kitchen where Suriya and Jyothika cook various types of dishes, together. The ingredient to a happy family? Agree? A family that cooks together, eats together and sleeps together, basically follows any discipline together, stays together! Now aren&#8217;t these couple goals? Or let&#8217;s just say family goals!\nAll we can say is, a celebrity home doesn&#8217;t always have to be MASSIVE or LARGE but having a cozy yet branded home is luxurious, in our dictionary, too!\nSuriya&#8217;s Chennai Home Decor\nSuriya and Jyothika&#8217;s family is clearly obsessed with nature as their abode has glass walls and expansive windows to enjoy the vistas of nature. Suriya\u2019s family surely believes in a dining area hence the bungalow consists of a plush dining room which is also known to be large and accommodates a huge dining table that consists of seating for 8 people. With white and golden shade carpet and a wooden dining table with decor that says \u2018High-Class only\u2019, makes it a dining area of a lifetime. Orange and beige seats and hanging round lamps right above the dining table adds an edge. We wonder if both are involved in the decor or is it just Jyothika\u2019s vibe!\nA bungalow and no stairs? Not possible. Suriya&#8217;s Chennai home holds a majestic staircase that leads you to the upper floor. Their bedrooms are designed no less than a 5-star hotel. The feels, the decor, the shades used for furnishing, all add up and make it look classy and sassy! With an outstanding interior and a pinch of metallic hues, is what combines the bedroom of Jyothika and Suriya&#8217;s home. What&#8217;s even cooler is the two-step staircase in the bedroom which, even to look at, gives elegance as a whole, to the house.\nGlass openings lead you to the balcony, which is mostly extremely dreamy and offers a beautiful view of greenery. Waking up to such a vibe is bliss indeed.\nA celebrity home and no theatre room? That sounds bizarre! Well, that isn&#8217;t the case at Jyothika and Suriya&#8217;s home. This celebrity home consists of a mini-theatre room where Jyothika and Suriya&#8217;s family is seen having a good time of their life. As the bungalow is being explored, it is pretty clear how this Sivakumar family likes to spend time with each other and bond. That&#8217;s a celebrity home for you guys!\nSuriya and Jyothika&#8217;s family does seem all about fun and bonding but when it comes to spending a few hours being grateful to the lord, Suriya has an enclave dedicated to spiritual pursuits. The bungalow is seen to have space specifically for a temple with various idols and where the family performs spiritual rituals and pujas.\nThe Bungalow consists of a couple of guest rooms in order to accommodate guests when they are over at Jyothika&#8217;s and Suriya&#8217;s celebrity home.\nA celeb home walk-in wardrobe is exactly what Suriya and Jyothika hold at their place. A wardrobe that opens up to a room full of clothes, dressing tables, mirrors, etc. it\u2019s all here which consists of numerous shelves, an area for hanging their high-end branded clothes, and show racks positioned well in the wardrobe.\nThe whole bungalow, when seen from the outside, looks in the shape of a ship, at least to us, with colours like blue and all its shades on it. It is pleasing to the eyes, it is massive and blue. Every room in their house has a different vibe to mingle and that is the beauty of this celebrity home. Nothing is connected, it is a different space, a different vibe altogether.\nA Glance At What Suriya Shivakumar Is Like\nBorn to an established actor in the Indian Film Industry, Saravanan Sivakumar, also known as Suriya Sivakumar is a highly established Indian Film Actor, Producer, and TV Presenter. Suriya&#8217;s estimated net worth is $25 Million. Now we know from where this lavish bungalow is built, kudos to Suriya and Jyothika as a family.\nSuriya is that Indian Film Actor who started off by making his on-screen debut with Nerrukku Ner in 1997 and after that did many commercial and popular movies some being Gajni, Perazhagan, Singham, Singham II, etc. and received multiple awards and nominations for his stellar performance as an actor. Suriya as an individual is known to be very simple, nurturing, and a man of emotions. He loves to spend his time gardening.\nSuriya and Jyothika tied a knot on 11th September, in the year 2006 and have been happily married ever since with two lovely children named Dev and Diya. Jyothika and Suriya met in the year 1999 on the sets of Poovellam Kettuppar. Jyothika comes from a Maharashtrian-Punjabi background herself. The actress herself has won many film awards for her movies and performances. The estimated net worth of the actress, Jyothika is known to be $3 Million as of the year 2020.\nAlso Read:\n\n\nAll you Need to Know about the New Parliament BuildingRK Studios\u2019 land bought by Godrej Properties in a deal of iconic proportionsBollywood Celebrity Homes That Spurred A Boom in Mumbai\u2019s Luxury MarketLavish Balconies of Bollywood CelebritiesA Sneak Peek into a Superstar\u2019s house: Nayanthara\u2019s Place of solace\n\n\n        \n            \n\t\t\t\t1. What is Suriya&#8217;s real name?                 \n\t\t\t\t\t                    \n\t\t\t\t\t\tSuriya, being his stage name, the actual name is Saravanan Sivakumar.                    \n                \n            \n        \n\t        \n            \n\t\t\t\t2. Were Suriya and Jyothika friends before their marriage