            "content_text": "Nayanthara is one of the most coveted superstars in the South film industry. The Kollywood actress shot to fame with two successful movies Manassinakkare (2003) and Ayya (2005), as her debut in Malayalam and Tamil industry. Being at par with her beauty, her fans can be sure of being awestruck by her abode located in Hyderabad. Nayanthara\u2019s house, a high-end apartment, is no less than what one would expect from the famous celeb\u2019s home. Every detail in the house speaks volumes about this celebrity\u2019s style and majestic way of living. Though having passed her prime age, the actress does not shy away from breaking barriers, whether they are with respect to playing roles in female-centric movies to standing her ground regarding the gap in gender pay scale.\nA Star is Born \nThis superstar does not need an introduction. Her achievements speak for her hard work in the Kollywood film industry. The laurels that she has brought from a very young age are worth complimenting and genuinely impeccable.\nThe journey of a brown-haired Diana, who was the epitome of an average girl trying to fit into the world of stars to become Nayanthara, the Lady Superstar of the Kollywood industry, has made the entire south fan-following quite curious. Nayanthara was 19 years old when she entered the world of acting, and since then, nothing has stopped this superstar from achieving her dreams. She went on from working as a part time-model to being voted as the \u201cMost Desirable Woman in Chennai\u201d by a leading publisher in Southern India.\nBorn as Diana Mariam Kurian, the actress later changed her name to Nayanthara and converted to Hinduism. She started as a model in college and was the first runner up of Best Model Kerala in 2003. At that time, she was pursuing her bachelor&#8217;s degree in English Literature from Marthoma College, Thiruvalla. She was later on discovered by the director Satyan Athnikkad who gave her a prominent role in the Malayali film Manassinakkare in 2003. She appeared as a debutant in this movie, which turned out to be a blockbuster.\nHaving worked in more than 75 films in the Tamil, Telugu, and Malayalam cinema, Nayanthara has earned a substantial fan following over the years. She is one of the few actresses who has worked with nearly all the leading actors in the Kollywood film industry. From Rajnikanth, Vijay Sethupathi to Dhanush, Nayanthara has worked with the best Kollywood actors and has maintained her spot, which is at the top, for nearly two decades.\nOut of the 68 awards that Nayanthara has been nominated for, the talented actress has won 66 of them.\u00a0 Her exceptional work in Sri Rama Rajyam (2011) was highly appreciated and won her the Filmfare Award for Best Telugu Actress and the Nandi Award for Best Actress. In addition, the actress had won three Filmfare awards for her outstanding performance in three movies, each from Tamil, Malayalam, and Telugu cinema.\nLesser Known Facts About Nayanthara\u2019s Life\nAlso known as the Lady superstar, she has been a part of the 2018 Forbes India celebrity 100 list with an earning close to \u20b915.17 crores. Nayanthara has bagged the title of one of the highest-paid actresses in the South film Industry. Owing to her splendid performances, she charges approximately \u20b93 crores for each movie.\nNayanthara was initially raised as a Syrian Christian, but on August 7, 2011, the actress went through Shuddhi Karma, a procedure that consists of Vedic purification and chanting of Hymns from the Vedas and Gayatri Mantra.\nAnother interesting fact about the south queen is that she is a polydactyl. She has a sixth finger on her hand, which is rudimentary, quite like the Bollywood star, Hrithik Roshan.\nNayanthara\u2019s Mystery Abode\nShe does not have an account on any social media platform, keeping her private life all to herself. We seldom see pictures of Nayanthara&#8216;s magnificent house doing rounds, either. The actress believes in living in peace without much flaunting on social media. Yet her strong persona keeps the paparazzi on the run, always wanting a little more.\nNayanthara has been all over the news for numerous reasons, one of them being her refusal to buy a permanent home in Chennai. She stated the reason behind this decision is nothing but security.\nIt is believed that Nayanthara\u2019s house is located only in Hyderabad. Thus, the celebrity&#8217;s home is where she resides to gain solace and solitude. Considering Hyderabad to be where the celeb&#8217;s home belongs, she prefers to stay in hotels while shooting for films in Chennai.\nSome interesting facts about Nayanthara\u2019s Home Decor\nNayanthara\u2019s house reflects her radiant personality. From the Italian marble-laden shiny floors to the high ceiling, everything mirrors grandiose and luxury. Situated in Hyderabad, this celeb&#8217;s home has the most aesthetically pleasing home d\u00e9cor pieces and artefacts that seem to be handpicked from various places. The luxurious space has a broad and open look to it. Everything from the furniture to the tiniest bauble appears to be at the perfect spot, and every element of the house is no less beautiful than the other. The walls are primarily off-white with yellow ceiling lights to complement the d\u00e9cor. All the cushioning, including the couch and the chair covers, are of neutral tone colour. The actress has cherry-picked neutral and muted colours for the furniture too. The false ceiling and the LED lighting together give a very royal and chic look to the place.\nLuxurious but Subtle\nThe main seating area has elegant white sofas with contrasting cushions that speak of comfort yet luxury. To add to the exuberant lifestyle of the actor, her room is adorned with glass sculptures that add a touch of vibrancy to this space, making it a centrepiece for all the parties hosted by her. With a television screen and wall speakers opposite the sofas, one can imagine Nayanthara watching one of her favourite movies in this spacious room which is nothing less than a private movie screening.\nBehind the heavy curtains drawn on the glass doors is the balcony overlooking the trees and plants. The green area surrounding Nayanthara\u2019s house spreads serenity and also helps the busy actress spend a little time in seclusion, away from the city\u2019s hustle and bustle.\nThe dining area of this celeb\u2019s home is just as magnificent as her style. Embellished with a breathtaking chandelier, the luminescence adds an edge. The kind of lighting in every part of the house is very well thought of and gives each room a different vibe. The dining area is connected to the main seating spot since the apartment spans over a large area. The interconnectedness of the dining and lobby makes the apartment seem large and extravagant.\nAll the bedrooms have a subtle d\u00e9cor with warm colours that are pleasing to the eye. From the exquisite curtains hanging in every room to the glass doors that open to fresh air, Nayanthara has not spared a penny to make this Hyderabad property an eye-turner. Ventilation is the most crucial factor in buying a house, and this celebrity&#8217;s home is the best example of that.\nThe spacious rooms have a separate seating area of their own. With recliner chairs and glass tables, the room itself has a world of its own. The walls of the bedrooms have a soothing white colour without the loudness of wallpapers. This can also be read as the actress&#8217;s choice of living, simple yet large.\nThe rooms oversee a scenic view that the actress can enjoy looking at through the huge glass doors. Or she can step out onto the balcony and spend a relaxing evening with nature.\nA Socially friendly Kitchen \nContrary to keeping the kitchen a separate hidden space from the rest of the rooms, Nayanthara\u2019s house has a huge open kitchen, overseeing the dining area. Adopting a contemporary concept of kitchen designs, the celebrity&#8217;s home has a modular look to it. The elements of modern design used to build this celeb&#8217;s kitchen are worth flaunting. A large tabletop with high stools is present so that cooking does not remain a lonely job but can be done overlooking the liveliness of the rest of the house. A sleek island unit in the middle of the kitchen is another concept adapted from the western interiors.\nEpitome of Elegance\nThe balcony houses a large hanging swing, which can frequently be spotted in Nayanthara\u2019s pictures. The balcony floor is covered with shining, new artificial grass that adds an aesthetic value to space, giving it a complete mini garden-like look.\nThe surrounding environment and atmosphere are perfect for the actress to practice yoga in her spare time and indulge in self-care. Moreover, the sunlight coming across from the glass doors would make a perfect morning for the actress to start her day afresh.\nThe ornaments and furnishings in Nayanthara\u2019s house cover every table and flat surface present in the house. These ornaments vary from colourful potted plants to beautiful mini sculptures that add to the radiance of her home. The abundance of house-plants surely points towards the celeb&#8217;s love for nature and its beauty. There is no over-the-top bling to the house. All the decorations are subtle and elegant.\nNot all Glitter\nThere is so much more to Nayanthara&#8217;s house than just fancy walls, glamour, and glitter. It has a sense of peace and calm. No doubt, she travels back to Hyderabad after her work to have a peaceful time at a place that she can call home. A home is a place that brings us solace. Nayanthara has built herself an apartment just like that. The homeliness of the plush furniture to the ornaments that represent a celebrity&#8217;s house is all a blend and balance of the perfect ingredients that one dreams of having in a home they wish to live in. The Queen of Kollywood sure knows how to live life Queen Size.\nFAQs\n\n        \n            \n\t